(Agentic Engineering Patterns > I use the term agentic engineering to describe the practice of) Tj
T*
(developing software with the assistance of coding agents. What are coding agents ? They're) Tj
T*
(agents that can both write and execute code. Popular examples include Claude Code , OpenAI) Tj
T*
(Codex , and Gemini CLI . What's an agent ? Clearly defining that term is a challenge that has) Tj
T*
(frustrated AI researchers since at least the 1990s but the definition I've come to accept, at) Tj
T*
(least in the field of Large Language Models \(LLMs\) like GPT-5 and Gemini and Claude, is this) Tj
T*
(one: Agents run tools in a loop to achieve a goal You prompt the coding agent to define a goal.) Tj
T*
(The agent then generates and executes code in a loop until that goal has been met. Code) Tj
T*
(execution is the defining capability that makes agentic engineering possible. Without the) Tj
T*
(ability to directly run the code, anything output by an LLM is of limited value. With code) Tj
T*
(execution, these agents can start iterating towards software that demonstrably works. Agentic) Tj
T*
(engineering Now that we have software that can write working code, what is there left for us) Tj
T*
(humans to do? The answer is so much stuff . Writing code has never been the sole activity...) Tj
